etaphors per page that explicitly link the Vertigo/Sight paradox to the Political Subtext (i.e., bureaucratic chaos, leadership, systemic decay). The philosophical concepts must be physically manifested in the prose.</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w:rsidR="00000000" w:rsidDel="00000000" w:rsidP="00000000" w:rsidRDefault="00000000" w:rsidRPr="00000000" w14:paraId="00000031"><w:pPr><w:jc w:val="both"/><w:rPr><w:sz w:val="24"/><w:szCs w:val="24"/></w:rPr></w:pPr><w:r w:rsidDel="00000000" w:rsidR="00000000" w:rsidRPr="00000000"><w:rPr><w:sz w:val="24"/><w:szCs w:val="24"/><w:rtl w:val="0"/></w:rPr><w:t xml:space="preserve">   * Example: &quot;The Vertigo was not a loss of balance, but the final, psychic record of a bureaucracy collapsing.&quot;</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w:rsidR="00000000" w:rsidDel="00000000" w:rsidP="00000000" w:rsidRDefault="00000000" w:rsidRPr="00000000" w14:paraId="00000032"><w:pPr><w:jc w:val="both"/><w:rPr><w:sz w:val="24"/><w:szCs w:val="24"/></w:rPr></w:pPr><w:r w:rsidDel="00000000" w:rsidR="00000000" w:rsidRPr="00000000"><w:rPr><w:sz w:val="24"/><w:szCs w:val="24"/><w:rtl w:val="0"/></w:rPr><w:t xml:space="preserve"> * The Rule of Three for Archetypes (NEW TECHNICAL MANDATE): All major archetypes (Astarte, the Unmanifest, the Curse) must be described using a minimum of three distinct, non-redundant sensory details to ensure immediate, visceral comprehension for a broad audience. (e.g., Astarte's Lie must smell, taste, and sound like three separate forms of corruption).</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w:rsidR="00000000" w:rsidDel="00000000" w:rsidP="00000000" w:rsidRDefault="00000000" w:rsidRPr="00000000" w14:paraId="00000033"><w:pPr><w:jc w:val="both"/><w:rPr><w:sz w:val="24"/><w:szCs w:val="24"/></w:rPr></w:pPr><w:r w:rsidDel="00000000" w:rsidR="00000000" w:rsidRPr="00000000"><w:rPr><w:sz w:val="24"/><w:szCs w:val="24"/><w:rtl w:val="0"/></w:rPr><w:t xml:space="preserve">II. NARRATIVE ENGINEERING: IRREVERSIBLE COST &amp; ZERO-SUM (NEW)</w:t></w:r></w:p><w:p w:rsidR=